Updates program image lists for consistency
Revises image paths across chess, basketball, and soccer programs to ensure consistency and include additional images. Removes duplicates and outdated entries while adding new ones to enhance the visual content.
Improves program presentation and organization.

Adds feedback form component
Introduces a new feedback form with fields for name, email, and message. Includes basic validation to ensure all fields are required.

Refactors FAQs into categorized structure
Groups frequently asked questions into categories for better organization and readability. Improves clarity by aligning questions and answers with specific themes such as program structure, registration, and safety measures.

Removes unused components and redundant code
Deletes obsolete components from the codebase, including a page header and testimonial grid, to reduce clutter and improve maintainability.
No functional changes introduced.

Refactors TestimonialCard component for reusability
Replaces hardcoded testimonial content with dynamic props for flexibility. Simplifies layout and styling while maintaining functionality. Enhances maintainability and scalability of the component.

Updates layout and improves job application UX
Revises heading structure for better accessibility and design. Enhances job application section with updated messaging and a dedicated "Contact Us to Apply" button. Removes redundant "View all openings" button for cleaner UI.

Refines FAQ and Testimonials page designs
Enhances FAQ page layout with improved sectioning and styling. Adds a responsive logo and an image for visual appeal. Refactors FAQ rendering logic for better structure and readability.
Updates Testimonials page to use a dedicated TestimonialCard component. Improves text and image layout for a more polished user experience.

Refines application and request pages layout and content
Updates layouts for consistency with unified styling Enhances textual content to improve user engagement Replaces placeholder text with meaningful descriptions Removes unused icons and address details for simplicity Introduces a FadedImage component for visual appeal

Refactors UI components and improves accessibility
Updates heading hierarchy for semantic correctness Improves layout consistency across components Enhances image alt text for better accessibility Removes redundant utility imports and optimizes styling
No issue linked

Standardizes heading hierarchy and improves accessibility
Replaces `<h2>` tags with `<h3>` across various pages to ensure proper heading hierarchy. Improves semantics by converting text elements to `<code>` where appropriate. Adds new components like `FadedImage` and updates forms for better usability. Refines layout and content structure for improved readability and accessibility.
Fixes #456

Refines staff card layout and styling
Adjusts spacing, typography, and hover effects for improved visual hierarchy and usability. Updates icon size and colors for better alignment with design guidelines.
Updates program icons and titles for various activities
Adds bio field to moreInfo in staffInfo type

Refines UI structure and improves component styling
Adjusts layout and padding for better responsiveness Enhances visual hierarchy with updated typography and icons Replaces generic button with a dynamic component for reusability Reorganizes content sections for clearer structure and readability

Updates UI styles and replaces icons with images
Refines the layout and styling of list items and testimonial sections for improved visual appearance. Replaces FontAwesome icons with custom images to better align with the application's design language. Updates testimonial content and author details for relevance.
No issue reference provided.

Enhances program pages with content updates and styling
Refines text and structure on Student Showcase page for clarity and inclusivity. Adds list styling to Programs page for improved readability. Reorganizes imports for better code consistency and maintainability.

Updates typography styles for paragraphs and list items
Enhances text readability by adding a base font size and line height to paragraphs and list items. Maintains consistent spacing and alignment across these elements for improved UI presentation.

Enhances school information page layout and functionality
Introduces a new `FadedImage` component to display engaging visuals. Adds a dynamic button for streamlined navigation to the contact page. Improves section layout with better spacing and text styling. Optimizes program feature grid for clarity and consistency.
Refactors redundant code blocks to reduce duplication and improve maintainability.

Enhances staff description for improved engagement
Rewrites the staff description to provide a more engaging, detailed, and inspiring narrative. Emphasizes the team's dedication, expertise, and contributions to student success while fostering a stronger connection with readers.

Updates staff bio rendering and HTML parsing Modifies the staff bio component to use a nested `moreInfo` property. Adjusts HTML parsing logic to standardize `
` tag usage. Improves data handling consistency and ensures proper HTML syntax.
Adds new icon images for basketball, comic book, extra, flag football, performing arts, public speaking, soccer, and volleyball

Improves StaffCards layout and typography
Enhances role text readability with tighter tracking Adds padding to description for improved spacing and layout
Removes unused icon files from assets
Removes unused herbarium icon from assets

Replaces static link with dynamic navigation button
Substitutes an anchor tag with a reusable dynamic button component to improve navigation consistency. Adds router integration for programmatic navigation to the "Contact Us" page.

Updates program icons for Chess, Basketball, Volleyball, Flag Football, Soccer, Creative Writing, and Comic Book
Replaces program icons with more appropriate images for Chess, Basketball, Volleyball, Flag Football, Soccer, Creative Writing, and Comic Book programs.
Fixes #123

Refactors FeaturedColumns component and adds dynamic theming support
Updates the FeaturedColumns component to improve code organization and readability Integrates DynamicButton component for better reusability and maintainability Adds support for dynamic theming based on the selected theme

Refactors school information page component and adds after-school program details
Implements refactoring of the school information page component to improve code structure and readability Adds after-school program details to showcase the benefits and offerings of the programs Updates partnerships section to emphasize the collaborative nature of the relationships Fixes minor styling issues and optimizes code for improved performance
Relates to #123

Refactors our_mission page with section tags
Refactors the `our_mission` page to use `section` tags for better semantic structure and readability. This change improves the organization of content on the page and aligns with best practices for HTML markup.
Fixes #123

Introduces FeaturedColumns component to OurCommitmentPage
This commit adds the FeaturedColumns component to the OurCommitmentPage, enhancing the page layout and design.

Updates link variant in button component
Darkens link text for improved visibility in dark mode

Refactors image URLs in AboutUsPage component
Updates image URLs in the AboutUsPage component to use local images instead of external URLs, improving performance and ensuring image availability.

Updates About Us page statistics format
Improves the readability and clarity of the statistics displayed on the About Us page by adjusting the formatting and scaling down the numbers. This change enhances the user experience and ensures that the statistics are easily understood.
Relates to #123

Updates ResponsiveLogo to accept a className prop
Allows customization of the component's className for styling purposes

Refactors About Us page to improve structure and layout
Updates the structure of the About Us page to improve readability and user experience. Adds responsive layout and images, reorganizes content, and enhances the visual presentation of the page.
Fixes #123

Adds new staff photos for Justin
Includes new PNG versions of staff photos for Justin and removes the old JPEG versions. Also adds a combined image with all the staff photos.
Relates to #JIRA-123

Adds FadedImage and ResponsiveLogo components
Introduces two new components, FadedImage and ResponsiveLogo, to enhance the UI of the application. FadedImage component displays an image with a faded background overlay, while ResponsiveLogo component renders the logo based on the selected theme. These components improve the visual appeal and user experience of the application.
Fixes #123

Updates program icons and descriptions
This commit updates the program icons and descriptions in the `constants/programs.ts` file. It adds new icons for the Chess program and updates the descriptions for Chess, Basketball, Volleyball, Flag Football, Soccer, Creative Writing, Comic Book, Performing Arts, and Dance programs. These changes improve the visual representation and descriptions of the programs.
Fixes #123

Refactors ProgramInformation component to use program title icons
Updates ProgramInformation component to replace the rendering of program icons with a single image element. The new approach improves code readability and simplifies the rendering logic, resulting in a more efficient and maintainable component.

Includes new icons for brush, bunny writing, butterfly, drawing, herbarium, scrapbooking, watercolor, and more.
